<subSubSection pageId="71" pageNumber="72" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="71.[151,1437,290,1000]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
Morphology. D VI + I,8–9 (usually 8); A I,8; P 15–16. Body depth 
<quantity box="[972,1087,326,353]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" metricValueMax="1.3462" metricValueMin="1.1938" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" unit="in" value="5.0" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="4.7">4.7–5.3 in</quantity>
standard length. Head slightly laterally compressed, with relatively short snout. The second and third spines of first dorsal fin longest but not elongate. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. Pelvic fins joined to form a disc, reaching to or extending slightly beyond anus. Caudal fin rounded, shorter than head. No scales on head and predorsal area. Body covered with scales (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Golani, D." box="[292,583,470,497]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="417 - 425" refId="ref58262" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Golani, D. (2007 b) First record of Papillogobius melanobranchus in the Mediterranean Sea and new data on geographic distributions, bathymetric ranges and morphology of several benthic fishes in the Levant. Cybium, 31 (4), 417 - 425. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2007 - 314 - 002" type="journal article" year="2007">Kovačić &amp; Golani 2007b</bibRefCitation>
), but scales poorly visible on freshly dead specimen photographs, visibility on live specimens unknown (
<figureCitation box="[478,562,506,533]" captionStart="FIGURE 61" captionStartId="71.[151,250,1973,1997]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,1024,1950]" captionTargetId="figure-359@71.[177,1411,1024,1950]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURE 61. Freshly dead coloration of Papillogobius melanobranchus. Photo by S.V. Bogorodsky, Gulf of Suez, Egypt, Red Sea." pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="71.[151,1437,290,1000]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
Fresh dead coloration. Whitish or pale greenish gray, the upper 2/3 of body with small brown spots of variable size, mainly on scale edges; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">body with a midlateral row of 6 larger and darker markings, mainly as double spots</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[225,306,614,641]" captionStart="FIGURE 61" captionStartId="71.[151,250,1973,1997]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,1024,1950]" captionTargetId="figure-359@71.[177,1411,1024,1950]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURE 61. Freshly dead coloration of Papillogobius melanobranchus. Photo by S.V. Bogorodsky, Gulf of Suez, Egypt, Red Sea." pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
), the first beneath pectoral fin, the last at base of caudal fin.A large indistinct orangish brown blotch on base of opercle. In males, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[442,997,649,676]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">ventral third of body with vertical orange lines</emphasis>
, some linked to the midlateral blackish spots. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">In males, outer margin of first dorsal fin deep purple, with an irregular pale yellow submarginal band; caudal fin with a dark spot on upper edge</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[664,745,722,749]" captionStart="FIGURE 61" captionStartId="71.[151,250,1973,1997]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,1024,1950]" captionTargetId="figure-359@71.[177,1411,1024,1950]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURE 61. Freshly dead coloration of Papillogobius melanobranchus. Photo by S.V. Bogorodsky, Gulf of Suez, Egypt, Red Sea." pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V." box="[768,1104,722,748]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="369 - 379" refId="ref58553" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V. (2013) Silhouettea chaimi Goren, 1978, a junior synonym of Papillogobius melanobranchus (Fowler, 1934) (Teleostei: Gobiidae). Zootaxa, 3613 (4), 369 - 379. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3613.4.4" type="journal article" year="2013">Kovačić &amp; Bogorodsky 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="71.[151,1437,290,1000]" box="[199,1003,758,784]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1973" box="[383,680,758,784]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Pomatoschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adriaticus">
