</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="71.[151,1437,290,1000]" box="[199,1330,794,821]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
Habitat. Inhabits silty sand and sparse seagrass, at depths of 
<quantity box="[876,968,794,821]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" unit="m" value="2.65" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="0.3">0.3–5 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V." box="[982,1318,794,820]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="369 - 379" refId="ref58553" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V. (2013) Silhouettea chaimi Goren, 1978, a junior synonym of Papillogobius melanobranchus (Fowler, 1934) (Teleostei: Gobiidae). Zootaxa, 3613 (4), 369 - 379. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3613.4.4" type="journal article" year="2013">Kovačić &amp; Bogorodsky 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
