<paragraph blockId="71.[151,1437,290,1000]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
Remarks: Often classified in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Whitley, 1930" authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1930" box="[622,938,938,964]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Favonigobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[622,776,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Favonigobius</emphasis>
Whitley, 1930
</taxonomicName>
; however, tentatively placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H.S.Gill &amp; P.J.Miller" authorityYear="1990" box="[1279,1436,938,964]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Papillogobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1279,1436,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Papillogobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the unique pattern of lateral line system papillae; see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V." box="[787,1138,974,1000]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="369 - 379" refId="ref58553" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V. (2013) Silhouettea chaimi Goren, 1978, a junior synonym of Papillogobius melanobranchus (Fowler, 1934) (Teleostei: Gobiidae). Zootaxa, 3613 (4), 369 - 379. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3613.4.4" type="journal article" year="2013">Kovačić &amp; Bogorodsky (2013)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
